Police detectives based in Migori were able to stop a planned robbery that was to take place at the Allaxis hotel located along Migori-Rongo road. The detectives laid an ambush where six suspected robbers onboard motorcycles arrived ready for the planned mission. Police said the six were ordered to surrender but instead fired at the detectives. During the shoot out,  two suspects were fatally injured and the other four escaped with gunshot wounds. A DCI detective was also shot on the right shoulder and is currently receiving treatment and is in stable condition. One AK 47 rifle loaded with 16 rounds of ammunition, a torch, a rungu among other items were recovered. Police have launched a manhunt for the other suspects.